#, no-wrap
msgid "`auth` - Authentication"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/security/pam.md:75
msgid ""
"This handles the authentication of the requester and establishes the rights "
"of the account:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: ../src/docs/guides/security/pam.md:77
msgid ""
"Usually authenticates with a password by comparing it to a value stored in a "
"database, or by relying on an authentication server,"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: ../src/docs/guides/security/pam.md:79
msgid "Establishes account settings: uid, gid, groups, and resource limits."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ###
#: ../src/docs/guides/security/pam.md:80
#, no-wrap
msgid "`account` - Account management"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/security/pam.md:83
msgid "Checks that the requested account is available:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: ../src/docs/guides/security/pam.md:85
msgid ""
"Relates to the availability of the account for reasons other than "
"authentication (e.g. for time restrictions)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ###
#: ../src/docs/guides/security/pam.md:86
#, no-wrap
msgid "`session` - Session management"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/security/pam.md:89
msgid "Relates to session setup and termination:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: ../src/docs/guides/security/pam.md:92
msgid "Performs tasks associated with session setup (e.g. logging),"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: ../src/docs/guides/security/pam.md:92
msgid "Performs tasks associated with session termination."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ###
#: ../src/docs/guides/security/pam.md:93
#, no-wrap
msgid "`password` - Password management"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/security/pam.md:96
msgid ""
"Used to modify the authentication token associated with an account "
"(expiration or change):"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: ../src/docs/guides/security/pam.md:98
msgid ""
"Changes the authentication token and possibly verifies that it is robust "
"enough, or that it has not already been used."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: ../src/docs/guides/security/pam.md:99
#, no-wrap
msgid "Control Indicators"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/security/pam.md:102
msgid ""
"The PAM mechanisms (`auth`, `account`, `session` and `password`) indicate "
"`success` or `failure`. The control flags (`required`, `requisite`, "
"`sufficient`, `optional`) tell PAM how to handle this result."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ###
#: ../src/docs/guides/security/pam.md:103
#, no-wrap
msgid "`required`"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/security/pam.md:106
msgid "Successful completion of all `required` modules is necessary."
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: ../src/docs/guides/security/pam.md:108
#: ../src/docs/guides/security/pam.md:118
msgid ""
"**If the module passes:** The rest of the chain is executed. The request is "
"allowed unless other modules fail."
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: ../src/docs/guides/security/pam.md:110
msgid ""
"**If the module fails:** The rest of the chain is executed. Finally the "
"request is rejected."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/security/pam.md:112
msgid ""
"The module must be successfully verified for the authentication to continue. "
"If the verification of a module marked `required` fails, the user is not "
"notified until all modules associated with that interface have been verified."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ###
#: ../src/docs/guides/security/pam.md:113
#, no-wrap
msgid "`requisite`"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/security/pam.md:116
msgid "Successful completion of all `requisite` modules is necessary."
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: ../src/docs/guides/security/pam.md:120
msgid "**If the module fails:** The request is immediately rejected."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/security/pam.md:122
msgid ""
"The module must be successfully verified for authentication to continue. "
"However, if the verification of a `requisite`-marked module fails, the user "
"is immediately notified by a message indicating the failure of the first "
"`required` or `requisite` module."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ###
#: ../src/docs/guides/security/pam.md:123
#, no-wrap
msgid "`sufficient`"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/security/pam.md:126
msgid ""
"Modules marked `sufficient` can be used to let a user in \"early\" under "
"certain conditions:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: ../src/docs/guides/security/pam.md:128
msgid ""
"**If the module succeeds:** The authentication request is immediately "
"allowed if none of the previous modules failed."
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: ../src/docs/guides/security/pam.md:130
msgid ""
"**If the module fails:** The module is ignored. The rest of the chain is "
"executed."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/security/pam.md:132
msgid ""
"However, if a module check marked `sufficient` is successful, but modules "
"marked `required` or `requisite` have failed their checks, the success of "
"the `sufficient` module is ignored, and the request fails."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ###
#: ../src/docs/guides/security/pam.md:133
#, no-wrap
msgid "`optional`"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/security/pam.md:136
msgid ""
"The module is executed but the result of the request is ignored. If all "
"modules in the chain were marked `optional`, all requests would always be "
"accepted."
msgstr ""

