#: ../src/docs/guides/security/pam.md:179
msgid "In `/etc/pam.d/password-auth` add:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block
#: ../src/docs/guides/security/pam.md:180
#, no-wrap
msgid "password sufficient pam_cracklib.so retry=2\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/security/pam.md:185
msgid ""
"This module uses the `cracklib` library to check the strength of a new "
"password. It can also check that the new password is not built from the old "
"one. It *only* affects the password mechanism."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/security/pam.md:187
msgid ""
"By default this module checks the following aspects and rejects if this is "
"the case:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: ../src/docs/guides/security/pam.md:191
msgid "Is the new password from the dictionary?"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: ../src/docs/guides/security/pam.md:191
msgid ""
"Is the new password a palindrome of the old one (e.g.: azerty <> ytreza)?"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: ../src/docs/guides/security/pam.md:191
msgid ""
"Has the user only changed the case of the password (e.g.: azerty <>AzErTy)?"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/security/pam.md:193
msgid "Possible arguments for this module:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: ../src/docs/guides/security/pam.md:197
msgid "`retry=n`: imposes `n` requests (1` by default) for the new password."
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: ../src/docs/guides/security/pam.md:197
msgid ""
"`difok=n`: imposes at least `n` characters (`10` by default), different from "
"the old password. If half of the characters of the new password are "
"different from the old one, the new password is validated."
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: ../src/docs/guides/security/pam.md:197
msgid ""
"`minlen=n`: imposes a password of `n+1` characters minimum. You cannot "
"assign a minimum lower than 6 characters (the module is compiled this way)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/security/pam.md:199
msgid "Other possible arguments :"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: ../src/docs/guides/security/pam.md:204
msgid "`dcredit=-n`: imposes a password containing at least `n` digits,"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: ../src/docs/guides/security/pam.md:204
msgid ""
"`ucredit=-n`: imposes a password containing at least `n` capital letters,"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: ../src/docs/guides/security/pam.md:204
msgid ""
"`credit=-n`: imposes a password containing at least `n` lower case letters,"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: ../src/docs/guides/security/pam.md:204
msgid ""
"`ocredit=-n`: imposes a password containing at least `n` special characters."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ###
#: ../src/docs/guides/security/pam.md:205
#, no-wrap
msgid "`pam_tally`"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/security/pam.md:208
msgid ""
"The `pam_tally` module allows you to lock an account based on a number of "
"unsuccessful login attempts."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/security/pam.md:210
msgid ""
"The default config file for this module might look like: `/etc/pam.d/system-"
"auth`:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block
#: ../src/docs/guides/security/pam.md:211
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"auth required /lib/security/pam_tally.so onerr=fail no_magic_root\n"
"account required /lib/security/pam_tally.so deny=3 reset no_magic_root\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/security/pam.md:217
msgid ""
"The `auth` mechanism accepts or denies authentication and resets the counter."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/security/pam.md:219
msgid "The `account` mechanism increments the counter."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/security/pam.md:221
msgid "Some arguments of the pam_tally module include:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: ../src/docs/guides/security/pam.md:228
msgid "`onerr=fail`: increment the counter."
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: ../src/docs/guides/security/pam.md:228
msgid ""
"`deny=n`: once the number `n` of unsuccessful attempts is exceeded, the "
"account is locked."
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: ../src/docs/guides/security/pam.md:228
msgid ""
"`no_magic_root`: can be used to deny access to root-level services launched "
"by daemons."
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '    * '
#: ../src/docs/guides/security/pam.md:228
msgid "e.g. don't use this for `su`."
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: ../src/docs/guides/security/pam.md:228
msgid "`reset`: reset the counter to 0 if the authentication is validated."
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: ../src/docs/guides/security/pam.md:228
msgid "`lock_time=nsec`: the account is locked for `n` seconds."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/security/pam.md:230
msgid ""
"This module works together with the default file for unsuccessful attempts `/"
"var/log/faillog` (which can be replaced by another file with the argument "
"`file=xxxx`), and the associated command `faillog`."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/security/pam.md:232
msgid "Syntax of the faillog command:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block
#: ../src/docs/guides/security/pam.md:233
#, no-wrap
msgid "faillog[-m n] |-u login][-r]\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: ../src/docs/guides/security/pam.md:242
msgid ""
"`m`: to define, in the command display, the maximum number of unsuccessful "
"attempts,"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: ../src/docs/guides/security/pam.md:242
msgid "`u`: to specify a user,"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: ../src/docs/guides/security/pam.md:242
msgid "`r`: to unlock a user."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ###
#: ../src/docs/guides/security/pam.md:243
#, no-wrap
msgid "`pam_time`"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/security/pam.md:246
msgid ""
"The `pam_time` module allows you to limit the access times to services "
"managed by PAM."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/security/pam.md:248
msgid "To activate it, edit `/etc/pam.d/system-auth` and add:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block
#: ../src/docs/guides/security/pam.md:249
#, no-wrap
msgid "account required /lib/security/pam_time.so\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/security/pam.md:254
msgid "The configuration is done in the `/etc/security/time.conf` file:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block
#: ../src/docs/guides/security/pam.md:255
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"login ; * ; users ;MoTuWeThFr0800-2000\n"
"http ; * ; users ;Al0000-2400\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/security/pam.md:261
msgid "The syntax of a directive is as follows:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block
#: ../src/docs/guides/security/pam.md:262
#, no-wrap
msgid "services; ttys; users; times\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/security/pam.md:267
msgid "In the following definitions, the logical list uses:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: ../src/docs/guides/security/pam.md:272
msgid "`&`: is the \"and\" logical."
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: ../src/docs/guides/security/pam.md:272
msgid "`|`: is the \"or\" logical."
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: ../src/docs/guides/security/pam.md:272
msgid "`!`: means negation, or \"all except\"."
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: ../src/docs/guides/security/pam.md:272
msgid "`*`: is the wildcard character."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/security/pam.md:274
msgid "The columns correspond to :"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: ../src/docs/guides/security/pam.md:279
msgid ""
"`services`: a logical list of services managed by PAM that are also to be "
"managed by this rule"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: ../src/docs/guides/security/pam.md:279
msgid "`ttys`: a logical list of related devices"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: ../src/docs/guides/security/pam.md:279
msgid "`users`: logical list of users managed by the rule"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: ../src/docs/guides/security/pam.md:279
msgid "`times`: a logical list of authorized time slots"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/security/pam.md:281
msgid "How to manage time slots :"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: ../src/docs/guides/security/pam.md:285
msgid ""
"Days: `Mo`, `Tu`, `We`, `Th`, `Fr,` `Sa`, `Su`, `Wk`, (Monday to Friday), "
"`Wd` (Saturday and Sunday), and `Al` (Monday to Sunday)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: ../src/docs/guides/security/pam.md:285
msgid "The hourly range: `HHMM-HHMM`"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: ../src/docs/guides/security/pam.md:285
msgid ""
"A repetition cancels the effect: `WkMo` = all days of the week (M-F), minus "
"Monday (repeat)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: ../src/docs/guides/security/pam.md:289
msgid ""
"Bob, can login via a terminal every day between 07:00 and 09:00, except "
"Wednesday:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block
#: ../src/docs/guides/security/pam.md:290
#, no-wrap
msgid "login; tty*; bob; alth0700-0900\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/security/pam.md:295
msgid ""
"No login, terminal or remote, except root, every day of the week between "
"17:30 and 7:45 the next day:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block
#: ../src/docs/guides/security/pam.md:296
#, no-wrap
msgid "login; tty* | pts/*; !root; !wk1730-0745\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ###
#: ../src/docs/guides/security/pam.md:300
#, no-wrap
msgid "`pam_nologin`"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/security/pam.md:303
msgid "The `pam_nologin` module disables all accounts except root:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/security/pam.md:305
msgid "In `/etc/pam.d/login` you'd put:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block
#: ../src/docs/guides/security/pam.md:306
#, no-wrap
msgid "auth required pam_nologin.so\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/security/pam.md:311
msgid "If the file `/etc/nologin` exists then only root can connect."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ###
#: ../src/docs/guides/security/pam.md:312
#, no-wrap
msgid "`pam_wheel`"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/security/pam.md:315
msgid ""
"The `pam_wheel` module allows you to limit the access to the `su` command to "
"the members of the `wheel` group."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/security/pam.md:317
msgid "In `/etc/pam.d/su` you'd put:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block
#: ../src/docs/guides/security/pam.md:318
#, no-wrap
msgid "auth required pam_wheel.so\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/security/pam.md:323
msgid ""
"The argument `group=my_group` limits the use of the `su` command to members "
"of the group `my_group`"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/security/pam.md:327
#, no-wrap
msgid "    If the group `my_group` is empty, then the `su` command is no longer available on the system, which forces the use of the sudo command.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ###
#: ../src/docs/guides/security/pam.md:328
#, no-wrap
msgid "`pam_mount`"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/security/pam.md:331
msgid "The `pam_mount` module allows you to mount a volume for a user session."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/security/pam.md:333
msgid "In `/etc/pam.d/system-auth` you'd put:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block
#: ../src/docs/guides/security/pam.md:334
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"auth optional pam_mount.so\n"
"password optional pam_mount.so\n"
"session optional pam_mount.so\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/security/pam.md:341
msgid "Mount points are configured in the `/etc/security/pam_mount.conf` file:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block
#: ../src/docs/guides/security/pam.md:342
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<volume fstype=\"nfs\" server=\"srv\" path=\"/home/%(USER)\" mountpoint=\"~\" />\n"
"<volume user=\"bob\" fstype=\"smbfs\" server=\"filesrv\" path=\"public\" mountpoint=\"/public\" />\n"
msgstr ""

